libxr
------------------------------------------
Cross-platform XML-RPC client/server library written in C that supports
persistent HTTP/1.1 connections over SSL and comes with XML-RPC interface
description language and client/server code compiler. Libxr depends on glib2
and libxml2.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.11-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.30.2-1
  libjson0-0.9-1
  libopenssl100-1.0.1-1
  libxml2-2.7.8-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-10-1
  automake-4-10
  binutils-2.22.51-1
  cygport-0.10.9-1
  gawk-4.0.0-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://oss.zonio.net/libxr.htm

Canonical download:
  http://oss.zonio.net/releases/libxr/libxr-1.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libxr-1.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libxr-1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libxr-1.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxr-1.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxr1-1.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxr-devel-1.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

